@sgouezel: Agree with the general point. There's however another naming issue related to these lemmas. There are three variables you can play with: `F`, `U` and `n`.

Something like `IsDynCoverOf.of_le` can work for the variable `n`, but how can I differentiate between `F` and `U`? I can't call them both `IsDynCoverOf.of_subset`.

Note that this issue is why you encounter `coverMincard_antitone` and `coverMincard_monotone_time` later on: there is no ambiguity on antitonicity, but `coverMincard` is monotone with respect to two different variables.

```suggestion
lemma coverMincard_mul_le_pow {T : X → X} {F : Set X} (F_inv : MapsTo T F F) {U : Set (X × X)}
```
